Changelog

Versions below 1.0.0 use MINOR bumps (0.x.0) for each snapshot you care about; list is newest first.

0.9.0 — current
  - Settlement: Est. net this period = included load revenue − fuel for the week (fuel tracked by stop date, not PRO)
  - Loads: Per-load revenue excludes fuel; dashboard charts use the same formula
  - One-time migration: recalculates stored `projectedNet` without fuel (gross − deductions − scale)
  - Fuel stops: PRO is optional — general fuel (no load); edit can reassign or clear PRO
  - Cancel load: option to move linked fuel stops to general fuel (default on)
  - Dashboard: Fuel this period — all stops in the settlement week, regardless of load
  - Loads: Cancel in-transit loads with reason (TONU, dispatch, requested, HOS, other) — kept on record, excluded from settlement and net revenue projections
  - Loads: Replaced non-functional delete with Cancel on Loads table and dashboard active load

0.8.0
  - Fuel stops: PRO picker is a searchable autocomplete — unpaid loads by default, in-transit first; optional “Show paid loads” for backfill
  - Loads: `isPaid` and `paidAt` on each load (database migration); reopening a load clears paid status
  - Loads table: Paid checkbox for delivered loads
  - Dashboard: Settlement projection uses unpaid delivered loads you select — not delivery-date guessing alone
  - Dashboard: View / edit unpaid PROs modal — include in estimate, mark paid when the load appears on your settlement
  - API: `PATCH /api/loads/:proNumber/paid` for paid toggles
  - One-time migration: delivered loads before today marked paid (`paidAt` = delivery date); outstanding loads can be unmarked in pgAdmin (see `tools/backfill-loads-paid-before-today.sql`)

0.7.0
  - Production: VPS deployment (Dockploy) with split API and frontend services; `config.js` maps usxicbooks.cloud to the production API
  - API: Versioned SQL migrations on startup (including drop of unused `FuelStops.location`)
  - Fuel stops: Removed location from database, API, and UI (table column and form field)
  - Fuel stops: Odometer on create/update; MPG uses the prior stop with the highest odometer below the current reading
  - Auth: Remember me on login — longer-lived JWT when checked, session storage when unchecked
  - Loads / dashboard: Mark delivered opens the load form instead of completing in one step; ending odometer required to deliver
  - Loads: Starting odometer prefilled from the ending odometer on the most recently delivered load

0.6.0
  - Dashboard: Projected settlement — open a modal to list PROs in the pay period; uncheck Include to drop a load from the headline total (choices stored in localStorage per closing Wednesday)
  - Dashboard: Edit the in-transit load opens the full load form in a modal without leaving the dashboard
  - Refactor: Shared `LoadFormDialog` and `loadFormUtils` used by Loads and Dashboard

0.5.0
  - Full remote deployment: API on Railway, database migrated to Supabase PostgreSQL
  - Dashboard: Projected Settlement Revenue widget (current period, centered)
  - Auth: Auto-redirect to login on expired session (401 interceptor)
  - Bugfix: All Redux slices and components now use config.js for API URL (were hardcoded to localhost)

0.4.0
  - Fixed some dependency mismatching causing render issues on the frontend
  - Added logic to calculate total deductions on loads screen
  - QOL adjustments for FuelStop component
  - Workflow improvements to Dashboard (fuel stop for current active load from dashboard)
  - Overall QOL improvements to user onboarding
  - QOL adjustments to menu
  - Donation link
  - Move changelog to separate file for revision notifications

0.3.0
  - User settings for standard deductions (MRP, IFTA, bond, etc.) in database
  - Same settings exposed on API (GET/PUT)
  - Standard deductions tab in User Settings UI

0.2.0
  - First iteration public beta release
  - Error logging and reporting on backend
  - Bug reporting feature
  - Separation of categories on Settings

0.1.0
  - Refactor codebase
  - Fuel discount settlements
  - Store all deductions in DB
  - Fix decimal termination in monetary values
